	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sounds good. So lets review here, people want this dongle to need/contain these things:
<br />
<br />audio re-routing from the cart
<br />
<br />a famicom-style DB15 expansion port
<br />
<br />a cartidge lockout chip that get rerouted through a homebrew cart to save on the number of real NES carts that need to get smashed to make said carts work
<br />
<br />an audio input and possibly an audio output
<br />
<br />an NMI based freeze / pause function
<br />
<br />anything else? I think all of this is quite do-able and could possibly be mass produced (not by me, remember!) once a source for the custom conector can be found.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
