		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I read in a document somewhere that it was possible to freeze games through the NMI on the expansion port. Maybe I read it wrond or the document itself was wrong, but it sounded like it would not be too hard. Oh well, I guess that one can be put to rest for now. I suppose the first thing is designing/finding a connector for that pesky port.
<br />
<br />I heard that in other projects pin 18 (am I correct?) on the cartridge port has been used in the past for audio expansion with converters, so I think that I could do that just for the sake of consistency.

		

